BEGIN_TEXT
Find an equation of the circle with center at the origin and passing through
\(($a,$b)\) in the form of 
\((x-A)^2+(y-B)^2=C\) where \(A, B, C\) are constant. Then
$BR $BR
\(A\) is : \{ans_rule(10)\}
$BR
\(B\) is : \{ans_rule(10)\}
$BR
\(C\) is : \{ans_rule(10)\}
$BR 
END_TEXT

$ans1 = 0;
$ans2 = 0;
$ans3 = $a**2+$b**2;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

